In light of the recent alleged abuse of the calendar, I say we put to vote a common agreement. (Not a rule, cause the calendar is an aid, not a standard)<br>
<br>
A simple aye or nay will suffice.<br>
The topic;<br>
 Should open raids only be hostable by those who are not in a planes capable guild, or by those who are unguilded. <br>
Meaning;<br>
If a member of a guild that is planar capable posts a reservation, that reservation should be counted as a guild reservation, not an open reservation.<br>
<br>
Aye... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaenae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aenae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 325<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/01 12:38:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=582.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/aenae_luclin/Attacking.jpg WIDTH = 109 HEIGHT = 267></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Nay, I completely disagree</span><hr size=1> IMO anyone who wants can host an open raid.  The problem lies in the fact that it must be OPEN, and the fact that there are a lot of them.  As someone who has led a lot of open raids myself, here are my personal suggestions.<br>
<br>
OPEN means a common signup point (here probably).  You should probably also discuss the looting system in your post.<br>
<br>
OPEN means anyone can come - no matter what their guild affiliation.  If your raid can only support a limited number of people so that you have to turn some folks down, thats OK.  Example.  &quot;Sorry we have 23 paladins already, I'm sure you're cool and all but one more isn't really needed.&quot;  But if your raid consists of more than 50% guild members or allies (Say Triad and MoM) then you should really mark it down as an official guild raid and not an OPEN one.<br>
<br>
OPEN also means that you have on additional restriction - you should have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    no more than one <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    upcoming</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> raid on the calendar.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  If you want to host raids on every Monday, great!  Post that you are holding an OPEN raid on Monday.  Lead the raid, kill stuff, have fun.  Raid completes, next day you check the calendar and see next monday is still available, reserve it for your OPEN raid.  It may become generally known that you lead raids on certain dates (me in PoG for example) - so be it.  I used to lead a lot of them and had a great time =)  But if someone else (either a guild or an individual) wants to lead a raid on a certain day then they should be able to also without having to wait three weeks for an opening due to multiple bookings*.<br>
<br>
The reasoning for this restriction is simple.  For a guild raid, advance planning is necessary to make sure I have enough people coming to get the job done.  People have schedules, other commitments, or whatever.  On a truly OPEN raid you shouldn't have any problems finding people because you have the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    entire server population to draw on</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  If I was to post that I was going to Fear next tuesday and if you wanted to come post below this message, I would get responses.  Lots of them.  You will too.<br>
<br>
*Caveat - I have only reserved PoG once in my life, every other trip was a pickup raid drawing on Triad, MoM, LoS, IB, Tiarcs, Apex, etc etc etc.  Even the reservation was an open one. <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/aenae_luclin/Priestess_of_Luclin.JPG></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaenae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aenae</A> at: 1/31/01 1:10:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 272<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/01 12:53:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=582.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nay, I completely disagree</span><hr size=1> I can live with those rules.  I like them.<br>
